        <section id="how-we-use">
            <h2>üéØ How We Use Your Data</h2>

            <h3>Core Functions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Sign you in with your Gmail account</li>
                <li><strong>Email Display:</strong> Show list of emails for preview</li>
                <li><strong>Archive Action:</strong> Archive emails you select</li>
                <li><strong>Undo Feature:</strong> Allow restoration within 30 seconds</li>
                <li><strong>Statistics:</strong> Display unread count and large email count</li>
                <li><strong>Top Senders:</strong> Show list of most-emailed senders</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Data NOT Used For</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Marketing or advertising</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Profiling or behavioral analysis</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Sharing with third parties</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Building user profiles</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> A/B testing or experimentation</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Selling to data brokers</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="section-divider"></div>

        <section id="storage">
            <h2>üîê Data Storage & Security</h2>

            <h3>Where Data Is Stored</h3>
            <p><strong>Locally on Your Device:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Extension storage (chrome.storage.local)</li>
                <li>Encrypted by Chrome/OS</li>
                <li>NOT transmitted to servers</li>
                <li>NOT backed up to cloud</li>
                <li>Only accessible by this extension</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>On Google's Servers:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your emails (in Gmail)</li>
                <li>Access logs (standard Google logging)</li>
                <li>Governed by Google's Privacy Policy</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>NOT Stored Anywhere:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Our servers (we have none for this data)</li>
                <li>Third-party analytics services</li>
                <li>Advertising networks</li>
                <li>Cloud backup services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Security Measures</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>OAuth 2.0:</strong> Industry-standard authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Token Expiration:</strong> Tokens expire after 1 hour</li>
                <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Data never leaves your device</li>
                <li><strong>No Passwords:</strong> Passwords never handled by extension</li>
                <li><strong>User Control:</strong> Can revoke access anytime</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Data Retention</h3>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Data Type</th>
                        <th>Retention Period</th>
                        <th>Deletion Trigger</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>OAuth Token</td>
                        <td>1 hour (auto-refresh) or until logout</td>
                        <td>Sign Out or extension uninstall</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Email Address</td>
                        <td>Until logout</td>
                        <td>Sign Out</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Settings/Preferences</td>
                        <td>Until cleared</td>
                        <td>Clear all site data or uninstall</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Undo State</td>
                        <td>30 seconds</td>
                        <td>Auto-deleted after 30 seconds</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Email List (Memory)</td>
                        <td>Current session</td>
                        <td>Extension closed or refreshed</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

        <div class="section-divider"></div>

        <section id="controls">
            <h2>üéÆ Your Privacy Controls</h2>

            <h3>Sign Out</h3>
            <p>Click "Sign Out" in the extension to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Immediately delete all stored data</li>
                <li>Revoke Gmail API access</li>
                <li>Clear OAuth tokens</li>
                <li>Return to login screen</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Clear Extension Data</h3>
            <p>Go to chrome://extensions/ ‚Üí Extension Details ‚Üí "Clear all site data"</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Removes all stored information</li>
                <li>Resets extension to default state</li>
                <li>Does NOT uninstall extension</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Revoke Google Access</h3>
            <p>Visit <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank">Google Account Permissions</a></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Remove "Gmail Smart Cleaner" access</li>
                <li>Blocks all future API requests</li>
                <li>Extension cannot access Gmail anymore</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Uninstall Extension</h3>
            <p>Go to chrome://extensions/ ‚Üí "Remove"</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Deletes all extension files</li>
                <li>Removes all stored data</li>
                <li>Complete removal from Chrome</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Privacy in Chrome</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Extension respects Chrome's privacy settings</li>
                <li>No cross-site tracking</li>
                <li>No fingerprinting</li>
                <li>No persistent unique identifiers</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="section-divider"></div>

        <section id="third-party">
            <h2>üîó Third-Party Services</h2>

            <h3>Google Gmail API</h3>
            <p><strong>What we share:</strong> Email metadata for archiving/deletion operations</p>
            <p><strong>Why:</strong> Required to access and modify emails</p>
            <p><strong>Google's Privacy:</strong> Governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a></p>
            <p><strong>Your Control:</strong> Revoke at any time via <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank">Google Account Permissions</a></p>

            <h3>No Other Third Parties</h3>
            <p>Extension does NOT use:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Analytics services (Google Analytics, Mixpanel, etc.)</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Crash reporting (Sentry, Bugsnag, etc.)</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Advertising networks</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Marketing services</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> CDNs for content delivery</li>
                <li><span class="cross">‚úó</span> Cloud storage services</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

