                <ul>
                    <li>Review this policy (you're reading it!)</li>
                    <li>Check the <a href="https://github.com/srwaditya/gmail-smart-cleaner" target="_blank">source code on GitHub</a> (open source)</li>
                    <li>Review Chrome Web Store listing for contact information</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>Data Subject Rights</h3>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Know what data we store</li>
                <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Remove all your data anytime</li>
                <li><strong>Control:</strong> Manage permissions via Chrome</li>
                <li><strong>Revoke:</strong> Withdraw Google API access</li>
                <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Understand how we use data</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>GDPR Compliance</h3>
            <p>If you're in the EU, you have GDPR rights:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Right to access your personal data</li>
                <li>Right to delete your data</li>
                <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
                <li>Right to data portability</li>
                <li>Right to withdraw consent</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Our extension respects these rights through the controls listed above.</p>
        </section>

